There are so many ways to harmonize that scale. I use two basic
harmonizations. 1) Levine, in his jazz piano book, gives a nice
harmonization using just two shapes that I like a lot. One shape looks
like a dom13(b9), no root. The other one looks like a min9 with a Maj
7 and no root. 2) A more basic, inside approach is to  just use a
flying lead for the notes in between chord tones. Sometimes I
harmonize the flying lead a minor tenth below. I probably stole that
from Joe Pass, who does it a lot.
