Harmonize this [or any other scale] by writing it on the staff. Then pick
out the intervals above each scale degree to get some basic voicings. Play
them on the keyboard. Some of the root position stuff with close intervals
can be played on guitar and some can't so work out some inversions that you
can use. You can really have a ball exploring some of these possibilities.

As far as practicing goes it's important to focus on very specific things.
When you get zeroed in on a particular passage it becomes a question of
repetition; every finger, every string throughout the entire range of the
instrument. It's just like anything else, really.

